76561198042252901,Recommended,512220,30473678,Posted: 12 March,all,Galahad,"This game is wonderful, I'll start by saying thatIts exactly what you'd hope for in a VR fantasy game, and it's still in early access,the devs are doing a great job and I really have only praise for this game but I'll try and be as critical as I can to give a balanced view for those questioning wether to buySo I'm using a HTC VIVE, not sure how it is on the rift but I'd assume much the samePros:Intuitive controls, the combat really feels natural and immersive, the enemys react great to different motions of the sword or where you hit them with an arrowThe vibrations of the vive motion controllers when you use a bow or your sheild is struck really make you feel immersed in the combatGreat sound design, doesnt feel repetative or out of place, each aroow loose and sword swung feels and sounds genuinely goodGood dialog, really reminded me of the early WoW games with the orc workers, good balance of humour in there, as with most things the only thing I would ask for is more of the sameMusic is on point, the right level of epicness, with the soundtrack changing for combat etcI really like the visual stye of the game, often when developers set out to make VR games they lean too heavily towards realism, but the playful style of the aesthetics makes this game feel fun and interconnected, theres nothing nearly real about it which often pulls me out of the immersion in other gamesThe progression is challenging, each new unlocked level has increased difficulty that provides thoughtful gameplayThe unlockables allow you to customise how you play, with different weapons or belt attachments, you can taylor your fighting style, I personally recommend the crossbow guns, they kick♥♥♥♥♥The enemies each provide different challanges, how you approach and fight depends on what youre fighting and how many of them there are, archers arent tricky unless in large groups, sorcerer orcs provide sheilds for others etcThe movement feels natural, you can adjust position by walking or teleporting, neither of which gave me motion sickness thanks to the comfort settings vignette that clouds the screen as you move, the movement is easy to get to grips with and allows for movement while in combat which is awesomeConsCan become slightly repetative, the quests soon crop up multiple times, you get used to them, but each level is laid out differently and the fun is in the combat more then the specific quests, and it is early access so you cant expect too much at this pointThe ballistas are hard to use, i found it difficult to angle them and see where I'm firing, plus the way you control, fire and reload can be a bit hit and miss, not great in high pressure situations, I tend to avoid using them at all now, perhaps a solution would be to have the player sat on the ballista, and they simply turn on the spot to rotate the ballista?Theres an occasional issue on the wave mode where the final orc doesnt come out, so you have to wait a little while, not a big deal just thought I'd mention itThings I think would be cool:I have by no means unlocked all this game has to offer so theres a chance some or all of these things are in there somewhere but I thought I'd pop them down anywayThrowables, potions etc that have different effects on the orcs such as freezing or fleeing, maybe having them turn to your side temporarily?Potions for yourself with differing effects, potions that make you giant or slow time, maybe just one that sets you on fire so as to harm orcs that attack youI love the special power of the ranged weapons and how it differs between each one, maybe something like that for the sword and shield would be cool, unless thats considered overkillOptions to customise the floating isle base that serves as the menu and where your gear up, nothing drastic just a few options to make it your own would be coolMore environmental weapons to interact with, boulders to knock over or mounted weaponry to use, the ballistas are a cool concept but more stuff to play with would be awesome-Overall this is a great game worth your money, I think it has a lot of replay value which is something lacking in a lot of VR games at the minute, if you're on the fence I really do recommend that you get it, it's a lot of fun, perhaps my favourite VR game out at the minute"
