76561197993554897,Recommended,512220,29547801,Posted: 28 January,all,zygoatboy,"A most excellent game. Completely emersive and unique VR setting, incredible combat mechanics and a great deal of all round fun. The game currently in early access, symultaneously infuses the player with the sense that they are a one person orc killing machine and also provides a robust challenge on some of the later levels.The weapon mechanics are intuitive and offer a range of tactical approaches. The orcs themselves have a range of different skill sets that one has to adjust to, and one has to constantly work with the procedurally generated environments on the fly to gain the tactical advantage. I have found myself sprinting for higher ground to spring an ambush on some approaching orcs, 'hiding' in some tall grass near the bottom of some stairs and picking off orcs or throwing myself into battle with axe swinging wildly. All of it sweaty, triumphant unbelievable fun.It ticks a couple of boxes as a VR game. There is a compelling adventure element, where the emersion in VR gives a profound sense of presence on the surreal floating landscapes. The ranged combat is slick and easy to learn, slightly more challenging to master, and up close melee is satisfyingly chaotic and exhillerating. The game's RPG elements are growing and I look forward to future developments.A couple of humble suggestions: It would be next level awesomeness to possibly have items or clothes that adjust movement tactics: shoes that allow a character to dash larger distances into the thick of battle to do wreak havok and then escape (alla Sairento's leap). Clothes that limit movement a little more but give extra protection or offer up extra powers and features. Would be amazing to tweak your character into a DPS assassin, rumbling tank or powered up mage. Upgrade to the current weapons (via gems or shards) would potentially give further control to the player to tweak and personalize their build and their tactics. Would also help alot with replayability. And of course more variety of bad guys. But looking at the range of regular updates and responsivness from the developers, it seems they have got all of it in hand.All in all, my favourite game to play with the Vive."
