76561198002049680,Recommended,512220,29752668,Posted: 6 February,all,Dimvision,"Trickster VR is a breath of fresh air in an as of yet undeveloped VR game market. The archery is on point (much like other quality archery titles), but it also mixes in other weapons as well. While the sword and shield, daggers, axe, and others are a little clunky for now, they definitely put a fantasy feel into this world and help to make the player feel like they are a real adventurer. With a few more developed quests/objectives, this will be the first step in bringing Dungeons and Dragons to VR.Procedurally generated maps are a great idea and help to boost replayability, though I would say that a lot of the similar ""tiles"" or ""sections"" of map are reused too often. This seems to be less and less of an issue as more maps are introduced, but it isn't totally randomized but rather a random piecing together of larger chunks.The developers look like they  have a good idea on the direction to take the game, and are updating with enough content that it really makes the development process feel like its going somewhere (unlike a lot of early access games). New items, levels, and monster classes have been added, and I would expect a lot more before they are finished. Definitely worth the EA purchase to pick it up every couple weeks for a few hours to dig back into the great existant features, and try out all the new ones they've added."
