,Recommended,512220,28987818,Posted: 3 January,all,Sir Buttercup,"Really impressed by the finish on this game. I've not played for long but fully intend to continue!The archery is almost exactly as I'd want. It may be exactly what I want, but learning to adjust between how archery is done between different games is a big part of VR right now. There were some invisible walls/sections which arrows wouldn't go through on some levels, but otherwise fine.Sword and shield, it works alright. To be honest I don't know enough to know how it could best be improved. The shield does block effectively, but it's way too easy to just waggle your sword in front of you and pick every enemy very fast.Throwing knives, the only thing I think needs real improvement (other than my aim) is the ease at which you can grab them to throw. I found it wasn't worth trying to reach down to my waist for them (even before my poor aim).There's a good selection of enemies. Archers, mages, some with battleaxes, swords/shields, some cast magic shields around other enemies making them invulnerable. The AI could do with a little improvement. They do sometimes get stuck or think they can see you to hit you when they're ever so slightly just around the corner meaning they only hit the wall/pillar.Map generation is very cool. I really hope the developer intends to do some missions in actual dungeons. The dark, claustrophobic environment would be very intense! But some of the darker levels, despite their place on floating islands, do offer a similar experience.There's only a couple of notable issues I've come across so far:1. Weapon selection in the starting area sometimes goes a bit mad. When selecting a newly unlocked bow, it selected it on top of my existing bow. I was holding two bows, neither of which I could fire, and I could no longer move around unless I was holding the weapon select button. I solved by restarting the game and reselecting the new bow.2. The blink effect while teleporting is a bit too extreme for me. The field of view while moving is made way too small, and by not having anything visible in the peripheral, it was just as, if not more disorientating than turning it off. Perhaps look at Google Earth VR. It may not suit Trickster VR perfectly, but having an indication of where the floor is when teleporting, and perhaps being able to adjust the field of view while blinking would make it that bit better.TLDR; buy it."
