76561198009435872,Recommended,512220,29102404,Posted: 7 January,all,KNEE,"This game may not be as polished as some of the more expensive titles but it's a blast for what it is. It's one of those games similar to what I imagined VR would be like before the consumer headsets came out. The levels a great, the design is spot on and they nailed the bow combat. There are a few bugs, but it's not a heafty price tag so they can be overlooked to a degree. The biggest thing I'd like to see is a velocity/distance based sword damage mechanic. At the moment the sword combat is it's weakest part, you can kinda just waggle the sword and things will die. Overall though it's a great game for the price and I look forward to seeing it's full realease."
,Recommended,512220,29461046,Posted: 24 January,all,Blargedy,"I originally played this game when it was first put on the steam store. Since then it has undergone massive massive overhaul, which shows the game is in active development. There are some good things about this game, and many bad. However, I have high hopes and will check back some time in the future, as I am sure the issues will be addressed.In my opinion, this game is more of an action game than a dungeon crawler, due to the frequency of enemies and lack or real exploring. This may or may not be your thing, so I suggest trying the game for an hour and refunding if you don't like it.pros:- there is a variety of weapons which all function very differently from one another. It encourages varied combat and allows for more tools to defeat the different types of enemies that have weaknesses to certain types and directions of attack.-there are a lot of options for VR comfort, so it is possible to minimize nausea.-The game runs well on my computer, which  has a GTX 1080. You would think this wouldn't need to be said, but some VR games stutter and lag and frame drop regardless of your hardware.-exploration is encouraged via the changing objectives and waypoints-the art style is consistent and feels like a fantasy world-the music is enjoyable.cons:-the music is out of place contextually. It will be playing super epic music when I am just backtracking and nothing is happening. It makes it feel silly sometimes.-there are too few terrain pieces which the game chooses from. I found myself becoming lost because I couldn't tell whether this identical gate->grassy area->large curved cliff was one of the 4 others exactly like it or a new one.-There are too few poses for the enemies. They will teleport if they run over a ledge or drop down from their airship. They will go from standing in front of you to having hit you with what seems like jerky and unnatural body movements-Enemies will literally go inside you and just cheese you to death. This was a problem in the original release as well. It was the primary reason I didn't have fun in the combat. That being said, the trolls are far less agressive, and will only sometimes go inside you. The AI of the enemy is fairly broken, since they will just charge at you one by one, often with pathfinding glitches, and BS shots that shouldn't be possible.-The collision detection with  weapons and shields seems very inconsistent, with trolls blocking hits they shouldn't, and landing blows they shouldn't.-The combat feels weak and unresponsive. Due to the aforementioned hit detection issues, the combat feels like you are swinging a butter knife in front of you with enemies sometimes dying and sometimes not.-The multi shot crossbow is far too  inconsistent. It feels like it only shoots straight half the time. That being said it is still super fun to shoot with against several orcs/trolls coming at you. Sometimes the reload twists won't register.-The world hub is confusing. I don't know what the color scheme of the boxes is supposed to mean.-Quests lack meaning and feel arbitrary. Mainly due to the fact that the environments feel so similar to one another, the one-quest-per-world makes exploring the world unrewarding. I only did two quests, so this could change in later quests.-The constant epic music and stream of enemies makes there be no contrast. It gets tiring and makes something that should be exciting become boring.-In the two missions I did, there was no variety in game mechanics. The missions functioned identically to one another. Go there, kill stuff, go home.______________________________________________________________________There are some great aspects, like the variety of weapons and the promise of finding new equipment, and then there are some bad aspects, like the terrible sword combat. It has great potential. The idea is great, the direction it is heading is great, but it just isn't there yet.TLDR; This game is mediocre but is heading in the right direction."
