,Recommended,512220,28684302,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,BowsersaurusRex,"Update: Tried this game again recently. Most of my issues have been fixed! :)I like the concept for this game, but it has a lot of bugs, even for an early access game. Movement breaks, enemy pathfinding breaks, enemy hit detection breaks (especially the lasers), weapon switching breaks, weapon reloading breaks, weapon firing breaks, weapon hit detection breaks, and all require a restart to fix.Completing levels is extremely glitchy. After a series of rapid respawns, the game will either dump you back in the hub world with the level completed, dump you back in the hub world without the level completed, or dump you back in the level with glitchy weapons. All three have happened regardless of whether I've died or completed the level.Melee weapons also need far more oomph. It feels like I'm swinging at air. I have no idea if my swings are doing damage. Adding significantly more enemy knockback would fix this.Also, using the grip for weapon switching causes accidental weapon switching when swinging a weapon.This game does a lot of things right, good graphics, procedural levels, great bow controls, hand based movement instead of head based movement, and properly using the playspace for dodging and cover. However, I'd avoid this game until the bugs are fixed."
