,Recommended,512220,29182183,Posted: 11 January,all,Reach,"This game is amazingly well done. Even in it's early access stages, it's the first VR title I've purchased that feels like a fully fleshed out game instead of just a tech demo or ""a look into what VR is capable of"" and the devs are actively working to improve the game with hotfixes and content updates.The meat of the game is the adventure mode in which you traverse through procedurally generated dungeons to complete objectives while fighting through a horde of angry orcs. There's a good variety to the enemies in the game, each with their own strengths, and as you progress through the campaign you unlock new weapons to kill them with.The other game mode is a wave defense where you protect your portal from an onslaught of orcs and shoot for the high score.Where I think the game excels above other titles though is how it controls. They have several movement options:Teleport - Hold the button, point where you want to go and appear there.Point and Move - Press up on the right hand track pad to move where the controller is pointing.Single Stick - Use the right trackpad to move forward and back based on where you're looking.Dual Stick - Use the left trackpad to move forward/back, strafe left/right and the right trackpad to turn left and right.The dual stick is my personal favorite and feels the most immersive, allowing me to move freely while fighting. I feel more titles should adopt this system as I find the current standard of teleporting in most titles disorienting. The combat controls are also well done. Drawing the bow feels great and wading into orcs with my sword and shield is incredibly satisfying.All that said, while the player controls are tight, the enemy AI could use a little bit of work. I've found on a few occasions that I can confuse the AI into a walking loop by dropping off a short ledge, allowing me to pick them off without much difficulty. Another problem I've encountered is that when walking around some of the more cluttered areas, I will clip on objects and end up getting stuck for a few moments while I navigate my way out of a pillar or a barrel.All in all though I've had a fantastic time playing so far and look forward to what new content the devs are gonna add to the game. I definitely recommend giving it a try."
